<AbstractNarration>This is the first year funding of a three year continuing award.   In this project, the PI will build upon his prior NSF-funded work to develop computer systems capable of operating autonomously in dynamic and uncertain environments.   Specifically, the research will focus on three major themes:  Qualitative planning under uncertainty using causal and counterfactual relationships;   Automatic generation of natural language explanations of actions, recommendations, and unexpected eventualities;   Learning causal structures from spontaneous changes, to facilitate predictions and decisions in data-intensive applications.&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
